node.text:
Introducing the @jacobandco Astronomia Tourbillon Art Skulls, a new piece from their Astronomia Art Collection showing why they’re the most creative watch company in the industry.

This timepiece is the one-of-a-kind Astronomia Skull. The dial of the 50mm watch contains a crypt of skulls and bones sculpted out of 45 grams of 18k rose gold intertwined among the well-known complications of this movement, which include the Double Axis Tourbillon and the two iconic symbols of the Astronomia: the 1-carat diamond that features the exclusive Jacob Cut with 288 facets and the magnesium globe.

The @jacobandco Astronomia Tourbillon Art Skulls combines high watch making with high art for a true masterpiece #jacobandco

node.text:
The jaw dropping @jacobanco Billionaire III. The 18k white gold case and bracelet are paved with approximately 580 carats of invisibly set diamonds arranged in a rarely seen horizontal pattern.

First introduced in 2015, the Billionaire unique piece adorned with Emerald-Cut Diamonds turned heads with its approximate carat weight of 260 carats (its price tag surpassing $18 million). 

Now, the collection adds another limited-edition Billionaire diamond-encrusted tourbillon timepiece, The Billionaire III.

@jacobandco combine their phenomenal watch making skills and true luxury with the Billionaire III. #jacobandco
